 between\nz~0 and z~3.25. In contrast, the component which dominates the bright end of\nthe KLF at low redshifts evolves dramatically, becoming essentially negligible\nby z~3. Finally, we note that within this parameterisation, the observed\nevolution of M_K* between z~0 and z~3.25 is entirely consistent with M_K*\ncorresponding to a constant stellar mass of M*~5x10^10 Msun at all redshifts.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Oct 2016 20:00:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-24"}
