rs,\nthe N2H+ column density peaks at least 5 AU outside the CO snowline. Moreover,\nthe N2H+ emission can peak much further out, as far as ~50 AU beyond the\nsnowline. Hence, chemical modeling, as done here, is necessary to derive a CO\nsnowline location from N2H+ observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Oct 2016 13:59:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-15"}
